ASSEMBLY CONCURRENT RESOLUTION—Directing the Joint
Interim Standing Committee on the Judiciary to conduct a
study relating to road safety.
RESOLVED BY THE ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, THE
SENATE CONCURRING, That the Joint Interim Standing Committee
on the Judiciary is hereby directed to conduct a study during the
2025-2026 legislative interim relating to road safety; and be it
further
RESOLVED, That the study must include, without limitation:
1. A review of the laws of this State concerning the operation
of electric bicycles, electric motorcycles and electric scooters and
whether additional regulation of electric bicycles, electric
motorcycles and electric scooters is necessary to promote public
safety;
2. An examination of:
(a) Data and other information concerning traffic violations
committed in school zones and an analysis of whether increasing the
penalties associated with traffic violations committed in school
zones would promote public safety; and
(b) Best practices for improving safety in school zones; and
3. An evaluation of the power of local governments, including,
without limitation, school districts, to regulate electric bicycles,
electric motorcycles and electric scooters in their respective
jurisdictions and to regulate traffic violations committed in school
zones, and whether additional powers related to these topics should
be afforded to local governments, including, without limitation,
school districts; and be it further
RESOLVED, That any recommended legislation proposed by the
Committee must be approved by a majority of the members of the
Senate and a majority of the members of the Assembly appointed to
the Committee; and be it further
RESOLVED, That the Committee, pursuant to subsection 4 of
NRS 218E.330, shall prepare and submit a report of the study and
any recommendations for legislation to the Director of the
Legislative Counsel Bureau for transmittal to the 84th Session of the
Nevada Legislature; and be it further
